                <h3>Step 4: Room Setup & Introductions</h3>
                <p><b>Room Orientation:</b>The room should have five chairs (or some place where two teams can line up on each side), and a central podium (table) where each person from the team comes up. A projector (or screen) should be setup behind the podium so that the game board is visible.
                </p>
                <p><b>Introduction to the Game:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Ask if anyone in the audience has seen Family Feud and if they can explain how it works.</li>
                    <li>Ask for 10 people to volunteer from the audience to create two teams. They should collaborate briefly to come up with a team name.</li>
                    <li>Have the game operator enter in the team names and launch the game</li>
                    <li>Printed answer-keys: enough for the participants, game-show host, and game operator</li>
                  </ul> 
                </p>
              </div> <!--col 6 -->
