        <div class = "how-to-play">
          <div class = "section-b"> 
              <div class = "row">
                <div class = "col-md-8 col-md-offset-2" >
                  <h3>Introduction to Game Play:</h3>
                  <p>Two small teams (5-6 people per team) compete in the Family Feud-style game. There are three main components of the game play:</p>
                  <p><b>The Face-off:</b> A one-on-one show-down  between players from opposing teams where a question is asked and the first player to ‘buzz-in’ (clap their hands) and respond with a correct answer gains control of the board - i.e. the right for their team to try and guess the remaining answers.</p>
                  <p><b>The Feud:</b> The team who has won control in the face-off tries to correctly guess all of the answers without first accumulating three strikes (one strike for each incorrect response). </p>
                  <p><b>The Steal:</b> In the event that a team accumulates three strikes before guessing all the answers in a given round, the opposing team has one chance to ‘steal’ all the points of that round. </p>
                </div> <!--col 6 -->
              </div> <!--row  -->
            </div> <!--section b -->
          <div class = "section-a"> 
              <div class = "row">
                <div class = "col-md-8 col-md-offset-2" >
                  <h3>The Face-off:</h3>
                  <p>To start each round of the game, one member of each team is chosen for the "face off" to see which team will gain control of a question. Traditionally, the contestants greet each other with a handshake before the question is read. </p>
                  <p>Read question aloud to the teams. After the question is read, the two opponents will clap (or buzz in) when they think they have a correct answer.  If the player who buzzes in first gives an answer on the answer board, reveal the correctly-guessed answers based on your answer-key.</p>
                  <p>If the first player to answer gives an invalid answer, then the player from the opposing team has a chance to guess. Note: No strikes are given for incorrect responses in the Face-Off round.</p>
                  <p>If the second player guesses incorrectly, then another member from the first team has a chance to guess. This continues until someone answers correctly, at which point they will chose whether or not to <b>play</b> the question or <b>pass</b> it to the other team.</p>
                  <p> If the team chooses to <b>play</b>, they will begin The Feud part of the game. If they choose to <b>pass</b>, the opposing team is forced to play the question.</p>
                </div> <!--col 6 -->
              </div> <!--row  -->
            </div> <!--section a -->
            <div class = "section-b"> 
              <div class = "row">
                <div class = "col-md-8 col-md-offset-2" >
                  <h3>The Feud:</h3>
                  <p>The team who has control of the board begins to guess answers on the board. This starts  with the team member next in line from the player who just faced-off. Team members may not confer with one another while in control of the board. </p>
                  <p>There is no time limit for answering, but the host has the option to start the one-minute timer built into the game board. </p>
                  <p>The player makes a guess and if they guess correctly, the answer is revealed on the board. If they guess incorrectly or fail to respond, a single strike is added to the strike counter.</p>
                  <p>Players on the team controlling the board take turns, sequentially guessing answers until either all answers have been revealed, or three strikes have been accumulated.</p>
                  <p>If all answers are correctly guessed before three strikes accumulate, a point per answer is awarded to the and the game proceeds to the next question</p>
                </div> <!--col 6 -->
              </div> <!--row  -->
            </div> <!--section b -->
            <div class = "section-a"> 
              <div class = "row">
                <div class = "col-md-8 col-md-offset-2" >
                  <h3>The Steal:</h3>
                  <p> If three strikes are accumulated by the team who played the question, the opposing team is given one chance to “steal” the points of the round. Members of the stealing team may confer with each other but must offer one answer.</p>
                  <p>If the answer offered is on the board, all the points from the round are awarded to the "stealing" team. If the answer offered is not on the board, the first team is awarded all the points for the round.</p>
                  <p>Any remaining answers are then revealed (formal discussion is scheduled for after the game).</p>
                </div> <!--col 6 -->
              </div> <!--row  -->
            </div> <!--section a -->
            <div class = "section-b"> 
              <div class = "row">
                <div class = "col-md-8 col-md-offset-2" >
                  <h3>Awarding Points:</h3>
                  <p>When the round is over, reveal any remaining answers to the audience.</p>
                  <p>Click "Next" or "Finish" in the bottom right corner of the board and add the appropriate number of points to the winning team's score.</p>
                </div> <!--col 6 -->
              </div> <!--row  -->
            </div> <!--section b -->
        </div> <!--how to play-->
